al theory, literary criticism, and cultural studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aLaw and aesthetics. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh  aaesthetics.  aargument.  aargumentation.  acomposition.  acreative nonfiction.  acultural studies.  aform.  ajustice.  alaw.  alegal argument.  alegal brief.  alegal interpretation.  alegal precedence.  alegal text.  alegal writing.  aliterary criticism.  aliving constitution.  aliving law.  ametaphor.  amusic theory.  amusic.  amusical forms.  anarrative structure.  anarrative theory.  anonfiction.  aphilosophy.  apolitical theory.  arhetoric.  asymbolism.  atext.  awriting.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092221140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520922211423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520922211/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles